      "text": " **Lemma 3** (Alexandrov's variational lemma, mixed volume version). Assume  $K$  is a convex body,  $supp(S_K) \\subset \\Omega$ , and  $f \\in \\mathcal{C}(\\Omega,\\mathbb{R})$ . Denote  $W_t = W(\\Omega,h_K+tf), t \\in \\mathbb{R}$ . Denote  $V_1(t) = V_n(W_t,K^{[n-1]})$ . Then  $(t \\mapsto V_1(t))$  is differentiable<sup>[7](#page-9-1)</sup> at 0, and :",
      "line_with_spans": [
