      "order": "17",
      "anno_id": 1,
      "text": " Let  $K$  be a convex body,  $\\Omega$  a closed subset of  $\\mathbb{S}^{n-1}$  determining<sup>[8](#page-1-1)</sup>  $K$ , meaning  $K = \\bigcap_{u \\in \\Omega} H^-(u, h_K(u))$ , and let  $f$  be a continuous<sup>[9](#page-1-1)</sup> function defined on  $\\Omega$ . Recall we denote  $W_t = W(\\Omega, h_K + tf)$  the associated Wulff-shape perturbations :  $W_t$  is a convex body if  $t > t_0$ .",
